title: Apex Oval
text:
Apex Oval, also known as Caltex Park is a sports ground located in the city of <a href="Dubbo">Dubbo</a>, <a href="New%20South%20Wales">New South Wales</a>, Australia. The ground is managed by the Dubbo City Council and is located within the East Dubbo Sporting Complex.
Opened in 2005, the Bruce Neads Memorial Grandstand has spectator seating for 1,340, as well as function rooms and other facilities. The ground has lighting and a capacity of around 12,000. As well as local sports, it has also played host to pre-season NRL games and the <a href="City%20vs%20Country%20Origin">City vs Country Origin</a> rugby league game in 2006. The City vs Country game was a huge success, achieving a record attendance of over 11,423 people. An impressive feat considering Dubbo has a population of around 40,000.
The ground is home for the Dubbo CYMS Group 11 <a href="rugby%20league">rugby league</a> team. It is also one of the home grounds for the <a href="NSW%20Country%20Eagles">NSW Country Eagles</a> team that plays in the <a href="National%20Rugby%20Championship">National Rugby Championship</a>.
In October 2020, the <a href="South%20Sydney%20Rabbitohs">South Sydney Rabbitohs</a> announced that they will be taking a home game once a year for two years to Apex Oval.
